# Known-good DEPLOYED binary baseline for `west darling-doctor` check 3.
#
# These are the md5s of the last-known-good deployed closure binaries in the install prefix. The
# doctor compares the deployed dyld (both copies) / mldr / darlingserver against these by default.
#
# Format: one "key = md5" per line; '#' comments. Keys: dyld, mldr, dserver.
# UPDATE this file (and note why + which Bead) whenever a legitimate rebuild changes what is
# deployed — otherwise the doctor will (correctly) flag the new deploy as a baseline mismatch.
#
# Current baseline (2026-07-04, task #116 A0-ARCH stage 2c): darlingserver updated to the
# A0-ARCH stage 2c landing (commit 5cf6081): ALL XNU wait-state writes (TH_* bits +
# wait_result) routed through ONE named-transition funnel (xnu_wait_state_write in
# duct-tape/src/thread.c, 9 sites) reported onto the per-thread state tape via the new
# thread_xwait_transition hook; dtape_thread_entering DELETED (its TH_WAIT clobber was
# the A0 disease) and doWork's preserveWaitState skip-dance replaced by a loud
# fresh-dispatch stranded-TH_WAIT assertion (recovery-clears like the old silent
# launder). Branch fix/a0-arch-redesign, see tests/A0-ARCH-STAGE2.md. Acceptance:
# quick gate 19/19 gating green (synth + both storm known-limit legs + brew xz 2/2
# strict), ZERO mstate/xwait violations across synth+fuzz+brew; perf A/B in corridor
# (nestwait 3627/3662/3625, 300xtrue 1s). dyld/mldr unchanged.
#   dyld    79b22273  (dyld-733.6, boot-compatible with the deployed 06-15 closure)
#   mldr    f0cd2a82  (perf#21b compact-fd band)
#   dserver 7692d9f6  (ring + A0 a3de8c2 + A0-ARCH stages 0/1 + 2a/2b/2c state machine)
# Previous dserver baselines: 47ac175d (2b, .bak in darling-prefix/bin), e50a3450 (2a),
# a889e85f (stage 1, .bak in darling-prefix/bin), 886d13af (a3de8c2, task #113).

dyld    = 79b22273481ea61ab63c0606c23ab300
mldr    = f0cd2a82efc4cb4614b63cabac0168f8
dserver = 7692d9f61b42223cbd271877e41d29bd
